class_data.Additional: Course Description: Calculus-based introduction to Newtonian mechanics. Topics include kinematics and dynamics of particles and systems of particles, conservation laws, rotational motion, gravitation, and oscillatory motion. Prerequisites: Credit or concurrent enrollment in MTH 141 and concurrent enrollment in PHY 273. Intended for: Science and engineering majors. Textbook: University Physics (Open Stax), 1st Edition, Volume 1 Available for free at https://openstax.org/subjects/science.
